Eastern Cape provincial head of the SA Social Security Agency, Sakhumzi Yawa died in a car accident this morning, his shaken brother Gcobani Maswana has confirmed to the Daily Dispatch. Port Elizabeth-based Maswana of Social Development said: &#8220;I&#8217;m on my way to East London to find out what happened, where. It&#8217;s as if I&#8217;m dreaming. This can&#8217;t be true. Yhini ubhuti [oh my brother],&#8221; he said before dropping the call.